	(21,1,'2018-01-24 15:24:06','2018-01-24 15:24:06','<header>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n</header>When you need to start, stop or restart the Apache (httpd) service on Mac OS X. And you are connected via ssh or telnet to the console terminal of the server, you can still control Apache (httpd) daemon.\r\n\r\nTo start httpd:\r\n<pre><code>sudo /usr/sbin/apachectl start\r\n</code></pre>\r\nTo stop httpd:\r\n<pre><code>sudo /usr/sbin/apachectl stop\r\n</code></pre>\r\nTo restart httpd:\r\n<pre><code>sudo /usr/sbin/apachectl restart</code></pre>','start, stop or restart Apache from the console terminal in Mac OS X','','publish','closed','closed','','start-stop-or-restart-apache-from-the-console-terminal-in-mac-os-x','','','2018-01-24 15:24:06','2018-01-24 15:24:06','',0,'http://home14.local/?page_id=21',0,'page','',0),
